Memory-extreme proposal: the smallest possible memory footprint, accepted even if it
costs some runtime.

Replace this file with the implementation and rename it with the selected language
extension. Choose the language by performance analysis for minimum memory (e.g. C, Rust).

If this proposal would coincide with the recommended solution.{ext} (a Pareto-optimal
problem where the fast + lean solution is also the leanest), do not create this file at
all - keep only solution.{ext} and explain in notes.md. Add this file only when the
memory extreme is a genuinely different, non-dominated solution.
